Key Match Events: Franses Mzize scored an own goal in the 54th minute, leading to Congo DR's victory.
Mbemba received a yellow card in the 46th minute.
Essende received a yellow card in the 68th minute.
Moutoussamy received a yellow card in the 72nd minute.
Salum received a yellow card in the 23rd minute.
Job received a yellow card in the 79th minute.
Saadun Hamoud received a yellow card in the 90+5th minute.
Pre-Game Insights: Congo DR and Tanzania return to action in the 2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers at the Stade des Martyrs.
Congo DR has won their first two matches in the qualifiers and seeks a sixth competitive home victory since June 2022.
Tanzania picked up their first win in the AFCON qualifying race with a 2-1 victory over Guinea.
Congo DR has named a solid 25-man squad for October's qualifying games against Tanzania and Ethiopia.
Tanzania's squad includes players like Mohamed Husseini, Ibrahim Hamad, Dickson Job, and Lusajo Mwaikenda.
